<div class="row g-4">
    <div class="col-md-6">
        <div class="encoder-panel rounded">
            <h6 class="fw-bold mb-3"><i class="fas fa-user-lock me-2 text-primary"></i>Control Panel Login</h6>

            <div class="form-check form-switch mb-3">
                <input class="form-check-input" type="checkbox" id="authEnabled">
                <label class="form-check-label" for="authEnabled">Require sign-in to access control panel</label>
                <div class="form-text ms-4" id="authEnabledHint"></div>
            </div>

            <div class="mb-3">
                <label for="authUsername" class="form-label">Username</label>
                <input type="text" class="form-control" id="authUsername" autocomplete="off">
            </div>

            <div class="mb-3">
                <label for="authPassword" class="form-label">Password</label>
                <input type="password" class="form-control" id="authPassword" placeholder="Leave blank to keep current" autocomplete="new-password">
                <div class="form-text">Stored as a PBKDF2 hash; never displayed back.</div>
            </div>

            <div class="d-flex gap-2 align-items-center">
                <button class="btn btn-primary" id="saveAuthConfig"><i class="fas fa-save me-1"></i>Save</button>
                <button class="btn btn-outline-secondary" id="signOutBtn" type="button"><i class="fas fa-sign-out-alt me-1"></i>Sign out</button>
                <span class="small text-success ms-2" id="authSaveStatus" style="display:none;"><i class="fas fa-check me-1"></i>Saved</span>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="col-md-6">
        <div class="encoder-panel rounded mb-4">
            <h6 class="fw-bold mb-3"><i class="fas fa-key me-2 text-primary"></i>API Access</h6>
            <p class="small text-muted">
                Lets scripts and orchestrators call the API when sign-in is enabled — e.g. pause/resume
                the queue or trigger a scan. Send the key as an <code>X-Api-Key</code> header or an
                <code>Authorization: Bearer</code> token.
            </p>

            <div class="input-group mb-2">
                <input type="password" class="form-control" id="apiKeyValue" readonly placeholder="No API key generated" autocomplete="off">
                <button class="btn btn-outline-secondary" id="revealApiKeyBtn" type="button" title="Show / hide"><i class="fas fa-eye"></i></button>
                <button class="btn btn-outline-secondary" id="copyApiKeyBtn" type="button" title="Copy to clipboard"><i class="fas fa-copy"></i></button>
            </div>

            <div class="d-flex gap-2 mb-2">
                <button class="btn btn-primary btn-sm" id="generateApiKeyBtn"><i class="fas fa-sync me-1"></i>Generate new key</button>
                <button class="btn btn-outline-danger btn-sm" id="deleteApiKeyBtn"><i class="fas fa-trash me-1"></i>Remove</button>
            </div>

            <div class="form-text" id="envApiKeyHint" style="display:none;">
                <i class="fas fa-lock me-1"></i>An additional API key is configured via the <code>SNACKS_API_KEY</code> environment variable.
            </div>
            <div class="form-text">
                Example: <code>curl -H "X-Api-Key: KEY" -X POST http://host:6767/api/queue/paused -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"paused":true}'</code>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="encoder-panel rounded">
            <h6 class="fw-bold mb-3"><i class="fas fa-shield-alt me-2 text-warning"></i>Notes</h6>
            <ul class="small text-muted mb-0">
                <li>When enabled, every browser request must present a valid session cookie.</li>
                <li>Cluster traffic between master and nodes uses the shared secret configured in the Cluster tab — it is independent of this login.</li>
                <li>Disabling auth rotates the session secret, invalidating all existing cookies.</li>
                <li>API keys grant full API access — treat them like a password.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
